                    <p class="text-big text-bold text-uppercase">What makes a Jurisdiction Crypto Friendly: from Regulation to Financial Services, Immigration and Beyond</p>
                    <p>The past year has seen the emergence of increased hostility toward the Crypto Ecosystem.  However, there is a light at the end of the tunnel, as several countries have publicly identified themselves as Crypto Friendly and are making inroads by creating regulatory environments in which crypto companies can thrive This presentation analyzes the challenges crypto  companies face in starting operations and proposes a methodology for evaluating and scoring the crypto friendliness of a given jurisdiction.</p>
